Use the standard library
This is how to modp of n and p:
   Remember that result is 1
   Remember that digits is tostring of n
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this digits's length times:
      Remember that d is item i in digits
      Remember that result is remainder of (product of result and 10) and p
      When d is item 0 in "1", then:
         Remember that result is remainder of (sum of result and 1) and p
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
